    "description": "HYOJITO Co., Ltd. provides advertising and promotional services in Japan. It operates through three segments: Navita Business, Ad Promotion Business, and Sign Business. The Navita Business segment manages advertising media in transportation facilities, including inside trains and stations, and is a designated provider at major stations and areas nationwide. The Ad Promotion Business segment offers planning, production, and sales of advertising campaigns, including mass media such as television, radio, newspapers, and magazines. The Sign Business segment handles the installation and management of outdoor advertising, including billboards and signage, with a track record of construction for JR Group companies, subways, and private railways across Japan. The company also develops and operates online media, including a tax-free shop search site, and provides digital signage solutions. It serves sponsors, location owners, local governments, and businesses seeking advertising and promotional services. HYOJITO Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1967 and is headquartered in Nagoya, Japan."
